WEBVTT

00:00.278 --> 00:03.201
<i>Kenny: The O'Neals had begun to
find the rhythm of our new life.</i>

00:03.365 --> 00:05.713
<i>My father had embraced basement living</i>

00:05.714 --> 00:07.895
<i>and mastered the art
of crock-pot cooking.</i>

00:07.963 --> 00:09.964
<i>And my mom filled in the greens.</i>

00:10.032 --> 00:11.899
<i>They worked together pretty well.</i>

00:11.967 --> 00:14.502
<i>My mother had even
started referring to my sexuality</i>

00:14.570 --> 00:16.270
<i>as "the situation,"</i>

00:16.338 --> 00:19.340
<i>which is step 2 of the 94
steps of accepting your gay child.</i>

00:19.408 --> 00:23.111
<i>Yep, things were looking
good, and then... </i>

00:23.178 --> 00:24.979
Agnes: I'm not tipping
you because I know

00:25.047 --> 00:26.948
you're a millionaire
back in your own country.

00:27.016 --> 00:29.117
Geez, who's the crazy racist?

00:30.185 --> 00:31.953
Grandma.

00:33.055 --> 00:34.989
Agnes: This is why I don't like cabs.

00:35.057 --> 00:37.592
Allowing you to live in
our country is tip enough.

00:37.660 --> 00:40.928
<i>Grandma Agnes, mother of my mother.</i>

00:40.996 --> 00:43.131
♪ Oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh, oh yo ♪

00:43.198 --> 00:45.366
<i>- A straight-up Catholic gangsta.
- [Rapping] ♪ We at war ♪</i>

00:45.434 --> 00:47.135
♪ Jesus walk ♪

00:47.202 --> 00:48.536
♪ God, show me the way ♪

00:48.604 --> 00:50.705
♪ Because the devil's tryna break me down ♪

00:50.773 --> 00:53.941
- ♪ Jesus walk with me ♪
- ♪ the only thing that I pray ♪

00:54.009 --> 00:56.010
♪ Is that my feet don't fail me now ♪

00:56.078 --> 00:58.446
Get the God box! Get the God box!

00:58.514 --> 01:00.048
<i>We're pretty Catholic,</i>

01:00.115 --> 01:03.718
<i>but we could never be Catholic
enough for Grandma.</i>

01:03.786 --> 01:05.218
Yeah. Pope swap.

01:05.287 --> 01:07.121
Francis down. John Paul up.

01:07.189 --> 01:08.556
Why doesn't your mom ever
call before she comes?

01:08.624 --> 01:09.857
Because then we'd be ready.

01:09.925 --> 01:11.859
- Jimmy, scatter these bibles around.
- Yep.

01:11.927 --> 01:14.028
- What are you wearing?
- Grandma's Easter bonnet.

01:14.096 --> 01:16.664
This hat made me 20 bucks
and change on her last visit.

01:16.732 --> 01:18.066
Suck-up!

01:18.133 --> 01:20.835
I'm not here to make friends.
I'm here to play the game.

01:20.903 --> 01:22.303
- We need to talk.
- Right now?

01:22.371 --> 01:24.091
- We're still married.
- In the eyes of the law?

01:24.106 --> 01:26.340
- In the eyes of my mother.
- What?! You haven't told her?!

01:26.408 --> 01:29.043
How do you tell the world's
most sinless Catholic,

01:29.111 --> 01:31.345
"I've decided the Bible
was wrong about marriage

01:31.413 --> 01:32.880
and I'm going straight to hell"?

01:32.948 --> 01:34.015
Probably not like that.

01:34.083 --> 01:35.383
Plus I'm not just getting a divorce.

01:35.451 --> 01:37.719
I'm divorcing the only thing
she likes about me... you.

01:37.786 --> 01:40.555
While my mother is here,
please just be my husband.

01:40.622 --> 01:41.190
Hey, wait a second.

01:41.191 --> 01:42.856
I've made a new life for
myself in the basement.

01:42.857 --> 01:44.726
I grew a mustache. I eat with my hands.

01:44.793 --> 01:46.060
I make decisions without
fear of criticism.

01:46.128 --> 01:48.329
Pat, you grew a mustache.
You are not a pioneer.

01:48.397 --> 01:50.031
Her visits only last two hours.

01:50.099 --> 01:52.500
Please, just go along
with this. And no tickling.

01:52.568 --> 01:54.902
- What? Old women love tickling.
- What?!

01:54.970 --> 01:56.738
- ♪ Jesus walk ♪
- [Doorbell rings]

01:57.116 --> 02:00.041
Oh! One more thing. You're not gay.

02:00.109 --> 02:02.310
Mom! So good to see you!

02:02.377 --> 02:05.413
♪ The only thing that I pray is
that my feet don't fail me now ♪

02:05.481 --> 02:09.556
Synced and corrected by VitoSilans
- www.Addic7ed.com -

02:10.457 --> 02:11.282
Mom!

02:11.283 --> 02:12.353
What are you doing?

02:12.421 --> 02:14.055
I'm hugging you.

02:14.123 --> 02:15.957
My goodness, Pat, that mustache.

02:16.024 --> 02:18.126
You look like a young Alex Trebek.

02:18.193 --> 02:19.327
Oh. [Laughs]

02:19.394 --> 02:21.696
Well, I'll take
compliments for $200, Agnes.

02:21.764 --> 02:22.463
[Chuckles]

02:22.531 --> 02:24.132
Stop! Stop! Stop that!

02:24.199 --> 02:26.300
[Both laugh]

02:26.368 --> 02:27.802
Um, quick sidebar.

02:27.870 --> 02:30.471
Um, why haven't you
told Grandma that I'm gay

02:30.539 --> 02:32.306
and you're getting divorced?

02:32.374 --> 02:33.908
Well, it hasn't come up.

02:33.976 --> 02:35.243
We talk about powerball,

02:35.310 --> 02:37.078
what kind of stone fruit is in season.

02:37.146 --> 02:38.626
We don't have time for idle chitchat.

02:38.680 --> 02:40.448
Mom, you cannot keep avoiding this.

02:40.516 --> 02:43.084
She's here now. If you
don't tell her, I will.

02:43.152 --> 02:44.752
Man, I really miss the days

02:44.820 --> 02:47.088
when I could shove a
binky in your mouth.

02:47.156 --> 02:49.791
Fine. I will do it. But
let me find the right time.

02:49.858 --> 02:50.792
Fine.

02:50.859 --> 02:52.794
Agnes: Shannon, here's $5.

02:52.861 --> 02:53.895
I love that bonnet.

02:53.962 --> 02:55.596
And I love all my grandchildren.

02:55.664 --> 02:58.266
I thought I'd have more, but
when your mother was born,

02:58.333 --> 03:00.568
she came out wearing
my uterus like a hat.

03:00.636 --> 03:02.303
- [Chuckles]
- Just like my bonnet!

03:02.371 --> 03:04.972
Oh! We almost both died.

03:05.040 --> 03:06.774
But then we didn't.

03:06.842 --> 03:09.143
But my perfect grandbabies make up

03:09.211 --> 03:11.112
for some of what I
lost with your mother.

03:11.180 --> 03:12.680
[Chuckles]

03:12.748 --> 03:13.756
What should we do first?

03:13.757 --> 03:15.817
Oh! Well, we could play
this really cool new game

03:15.884 --> 03:18.364
where we all talk honestly about
what's happening in our lives.

03:18.420 --> 03:19.754
That game sounds boring.

03:19.822 --> 03:22.290
Come on. I want to show you
my new colander in the kitchen.

03:22.357 --> 03:23.825
♪ ♪

03:23.892 --> 03:26.360
[Laughs] I have gifts for you kids!

03:26.428 --> 03:28.763
Shannon, I brought you a coloring book

03:28.831 --> 03:30.164
from my Sunday school.

03:30.232 --> 03:31.332
The theme is "sins."

03:31.400 --> 03:33.801
You see, these two men are fornicating.

03:33.869 --> 03:36.270
And I'll give you $2
for every page you color.

03:36.338 --> 03:38.706
Getting paid to color? What?!

03:38.774 --> 03:41.943
And, Kenny, I brought a jar
of my famous dill pickles.

03:42.010 --> 03:43.477
Oh, I love your pickles, Grandma.

03:43.545 --> 03:44.879
That's because they're thick.

03:44.947 --> 03:46.814
They have to be long and thick and hard.

03:46.882 --> 03:47.815
That's fine, Mom.

03:47.883 --> 03:48.883
No, no, no, no, no.

03:48.951 --> 03:50.351
I'm okay with pickle talk.

03:50.419 --> 03:53.788
And, Jimmy, my Bible study
group bought these clever puzzles

03:53.856 --> 03:55.556
for all of our grandchildren.

03:55.624 --> 03:57.144
We want to see who can solve it first.

03:57.192 --> 03:58.025
Be first.

03:58.093 --> 03:59.727
Neat! What is it?

03:59.795 --> 04:00.995
It's a genius test.

04:01.063 --> 04:02.783
You have to get rid of
all the pegs but one.

04:02.798 --> 04:03.631
[Chuckles]

04:03.699 --> 04:05.132
Uh...

04:05.200 --> 04:07.068
Bam!

04:07.135 --> 04:08.169
I'm a genius.

04:08.237 --> 04:09.403
Oh.

04:09.471 --> 04:11.172
I'll walk him through the
introductions, Grandma.

04:11.240 --> 04:13.241
Kenny, sweetheart,

04:13.308 --> 04:15.243
tell me what you've been up to lately.

04:15.310 --> 04:16.744
Yeah, okay.

04:16.812 --> 04:20.714
Um, well, I'd love to tell you
about it in detail, Grandma.

04:20.781 --> 04:23.222
[Clears throat] You know how
I've always loved "Dreamgirls"?

04:23.285 --> 04:24.652
We forgot to get cake!

04:24.720 --> 04:26.520
Kenny, let's talk about
it in the dining room.

04:29.124 --> 04:31.492
He always loved musicals.

04:31.560 --> 04:34.228
Mom, you're stalling.

04:34.296 --> 04:36.296
Trust me, it's better to
just rip the band-aid off.

04:36.331 --> 04:38.432
You know that's not how I do it.

04:38.500 --> 04:41.102
I massage the band-aid
with mineral oil.

04:41.169 --> 04:42.670
And then while you
watch "Tom and Jerry,"

04:42.738 --> 04:45.106
I slowly peel it back,
and then you get a cookie.

04:45.173 --> 04:46.374
[Chuckles] No! No!

04:46.441 --> 04:48.442
But it's not right. She's old.

04:48.510 --> 04:50.177
She could die without knowing the truth.

04:50.245 --> 04:52.880
I know you think you're
listing a con, but that's a pro.

04:52.948 --> 04:55.016
Come on, you tell her your
thing, and I'll tell her mine.

04:55.083 --> 04:56.183
All right, fine.

04:56.251 --> 04:59.086
We'll tell her together,
but after dessert.

04:59.154 --> 05:01.422
The sugar will make
her confused and docile.

05:01.490 --> 05:02.657
[Gasps]

05:02.724 --> 05:07.194
Run to the bakery and
get a lemon potato cake.

05:07.262 --> 05:08.362
Lemon potato cake?

05:08.430 --> 05:11.732
Yeah, it's a big Irish
thing. Potato cake.

05:11.800 --> 05:13.301
You know, because the British kept

05:13.368 --> 05:15.069
all the real cake for themselves.

05:15.137 --> 05:16.070
Bastards.

05:16.138 --> 05:17.238
- I know.
- [Groans]

05:17.306 --> 05:18.873
Yeah.

05:18.941 --> 05:20.942
This is when Jimmy went to state

05:21.009 --> 05:23.077
and Kenny won the debate finals.

05:23.145 --> 05:24.445
And here's Shannon.

05:24.513 --> 05:27.248
She won first prize at
the science fair last year.

05:27.316 --> 05:28.950
Such amazing kids.

05:29.017 --> 05:31.652
They really take after you, Pat.

05:31.720 --> 05:33.888
Oh, well, that's... Thank you.

05:33.956 --> 05:35.990
But they also take after my wife,

05:36.058 --> 05:39.160
who I'm still married
to on a continual basis.

05:39.227 --> 05:40.494
Thank you, Pat...

05:40.562 --> 05:42.930
Not only for the compliment
but for phrasing it

05:42.998 --> 05:44.765
in such an odd and stilted way.

05:46.902 --> 05:48.302
You know there's a scoop there.

05:48.370 --> 05:50.071
Sorry.

05:50.138 --> 05:51.405
Don't you dare apologize.

05:51.473 --> 05:53.841
I love to see a man eat with his hands.

05:53.909 --> 05:55.609
Oh.

05:55.677 --> 05:57.845
Oh, look at him eat like a gorilla!

05:57.913 --> 05:59.246
[Grunting]

05:59.314 --> 06:02.183
[Both laugh]

06:02.250 --> 06:03.784
Oh, good heavens, Pat.

06:03.852 --> 06:05.353
- You know what?
- Hmm?

06:05.420 --> 06:06.620
I've been wondering what to do

06:06.655 --> 06:09.357
with my Bears season tickets when I die.

06:09.424 --> 06:11.492
I was going to give
them to your cousin Gary,

06:11.560 --> 06:13.761
but he's still living
with that Sikh girl.

06:13.829 --> 06:15.129
You mean his wife?

06:15.197 --> 06:17.331
Either way, he's out.

06:17.399 --> 06:18.933
My dream was to give them to a son,

06:19.001 --> 06:20.968
who I wasn't able to
have because of Eileen.

06:21.036 --> 06:26.273
But it just occurred to me
that, Pat, you are my son.

06:26.341 --> 06:27.808
Bears tickets?

06:27.876 --> 06:29.610
I'll always be your son, Mama.

06:29.678 --> 06:31.846
Ohh.

06:31.913 --> 06:34.815
♪ ♪

06:36.685 --> 06:38.386
[Sighs]

06:38.453 --> 06:40.287
Damn it! I'm not a genius.

06:40.355 --> 06:42.289
- I'm average. I'm average!
- Okay.

06:42.357 --> 06:43.391
Okay, we're going to put this down.

06:43.458 --> 06:44.392
Grandma knew exactly what she was doing

06:44.459 --> 06:45.726
when she gave me the puzzle!

06:47.029 --> 06:48.462
Ahh. Okay.

06:48.530 --> 06:50.564
We have now been to five bakeries,

06:50.632 --> 06:53.167
and no one has heard
of lemon potato cake.

06:53.235 --> 06:56.504
Why would Mom send us for
something that doesn't exist?

06:56.571 --> 06:57.859
She's ashamed because I
can't solve the puzzle!

06:57.884 --> 06:59.064
She doesn't want
Grandma to know I'm gay!

06:59.107 --> 07:01.909
Why would she be
ashamed of the puzzle thing?

07:01.977 --> 07:04.245
No, you're right. It's the gay thing.

07:04.312 --> 07:06.213
That makes... A lot more sense...

07:06.281 --> 07:08.081
- A lot more sense.
- When you think about it.

07:10.285 --> 07:13.354
And aunt Sally's out of the
will since she went Presbyterian.

07:13.422 --> 07:16.424
- [Telephone ringing]
- Oh, my gosh.

07:16.491 --> 07:17.658
Yello?

07:17.726 --> 07:19.493
Kenny: Hey, Mom. Guess what.

07:19.561 --> 07:22.496
There's no such
thing as lemon potato cake.

07:22.564 --> 07:24.432
Are you sure? Why don't
you try a few more bakeries?

07:24.499 --> 07:26.000
You were never gonna tell her.

07:26.068 --> 07:27.501
I am saving us from her wrath.

07:27.569 --> 07:28.502
I'm coming home,

07:28.570 --> 07:30.171
and I'm coming out!

07:30.238 --> 07:31.338
Stay away!

07:31.406 --> 07:33.507
Go see one of those
long "Hobbit" movies.

07:33.575 --> 07:34.708
No.

07:34.776 --> 07:35.776
You know what?

07:35.844 --> 07:38.579
Maybe Mom is afraid of Grandma,

07:38.647 --> 07:42.383
but, uh, that ain't how
this eagle flies anymore.

07:42.451 --> 07:44.785
This caged bird sings.

07:44.853 --> 07:46.353
What are you doing, Kenny?

07:46.421 --> 07:47.788
I'm trying to speak for a generation,

07:47.856 --> 07:49.490
but it's... it's very hard.

07:51.460 --> 07:53.194
- Drive!
- Yep.

07:53.261 --> 07:55.796
All right, we've got 15
minutes to get my mother out of here.

07:55.864 --> 07:58.365
Kenny's on his way home to
blab everything to Grandma.

07:58.433 --> 07:59.513
Well, the father in me says

07:59.534 --> 08:00.894
honesty is always the best policy,

08:00.936 --> 08:02.103
but the Bears fan in me says

08:02.170 --> 08:03.370
let's get her the hell out of here.

08:03.438 --> 08:05.072
She's already criticized my housekeeping

08:05.140 --> 08:06.180
and talked about her will.

08:06.241 --> 08:07.641
Okay, so that leaves friends' illnesses

08:07.709 --> 08:09.160
and filth on
television and she's gone, right?

08:09.185 --> 08:09.685
Right.

08:09.711 --> 08:12.279
Hey, Agnes, how's Carl
Pilton's psoriasis coming along?

08:12.347 --> 08:14.615
Ohh. Did I not tell you?

08:14.683 --> 08:15.749
He's dead.

08:17.719 --> 08:19.887
Oh, no, no, no, no. We're
not gonna make it.

08:19.955 --> 08:22.423
Um, cut through this alley!

08:22.491 --> 08:24.931
Jimmy: Screw puzzles. I'm
a genius at driving.

08:24.993 --> 08:26.894
"Madam Secretary" was a good show

08:26.962 --> 08:29.663
until they started
dressing tea Leoni like a hooker.

08:29.731 --> 08:31.132
[Chuckles] So true.

08:31.199 --> 08:33.000
Thanks for dropping by, Mom.

08:34.469 --> 08:35.736
I got the cake.

08:35.804 --> 08:38.506
Grandma, I'm gay.

08:38.573 --> 08:42.576
Mom, do you have anything that
you'd like to tell her?

08:43.578 --> 08:44.612
Ohh.

08:44.679 --> 08:46.080
[Body thuds]

08:46.148 --> 08:48.249
Thank God.

08:48.299 --> 08:50.134
Mom, you'll be comfortable in here.

08:50.135 --> 08:53.767
Will these soft pillows take
away my grandson being gay

08:53.835 --> 08:55.569
and ease my general disappointment

08:55.637 --> 08:56.737
with this entire family?

08:56.804 --> 08:57.838
Hopefully.

08:59.507 --> 09:01.108
Have I died?

09:01.175 --> 09:03.343
Because Shannon looks like an angel.

09:03.411 --> 09:04.891
Thank you for the nightgown, Grandma.

09:04.913 --> 09:06.013
I'll wear it until you feel better.

09:06.080 --> 09:08.115
That's my girl.

09:08.182 --> 09:09.917
Hi, Grandma.

09:09.984 --> 09:11.952
I'm sorry that I laughed when you fell.

09:12.020 --> 09:13.954
Yeah, and, yeah, I
didn't mean to bring on

09:14.022 --> 09:15.022
one of your spells.

09:15.089 --> 09:16.857
I'm not ready to speak to you.

09:16.925 --> 09:20.394
Except to say that you've
ruined cake for me, and rainbows.

09:20.461 --> 09:22.396
All right! Nighty-night, everybody.

09:22.463 --> 09:25.432
Pat, let's you and I get into
our marital bed, like always.

09:25.500 --> 09:26.900
Mm-hmm. Righty-oh, lover.

09:26.968 --> 09:30.570
I cannot wait to cleave unto you.

09:30.638 --> 09:31.638
[Door closes]

09:33.341 --> 09:34.641
Good job, Kenny.

09:34.709 --> 09:37.144
What? Me? You broke our pact.

09:37.211 --> 09:38.578
I did not break our pact.

09:38.646 --> 09:40.614
I lied to you when I
said there was a pact.

09:40.682 --> 09:42.115
Well, then, you owe
me $23.50 for the cake

09:42.183 --> 09:43.617
'cause it has seven rainbow layers,

09:43.685 --> 09:44.918
and it's adorable.

09:44.986 --> 09:45.919
Wait, you guys are gonna spend the night

09:45.987 --> 09:46.920
in the same room together?

09:46.988 --> 09:48.188
With Dad's mustache?

09:48.256 --> 09:51.458
Yes, because Dad's
mustache is Mom's beard.

09:51.526 --> 09:52.459
Wait, what? No.

09:52.527 --> 09:53.660
It's just one night.

09:53.728 --> 09:54.995
It's not the end of the world.

09:55.063 --> 09:56.163
Well, let me tell you,

09:56.230 --> 09:58.131
as someone who had a beard named Mimi,

09:58.199 --> 10:00.634
that's gonna get itchy
and bitchy real quick.

10:00.702 --> 10:02.135
- Excuse me?
- I get it, okay?

10:02.203 --> 10:03.503
It stinks a little bit,

10:03.571 --> 10:04.938
but it's just 'cause I
got some food caught in it,

10:05.006 --> 10:06.106
and I can't find it.

10:06.174 --> 10:07.975
Kenneth Christopher Sebastian O'Neal,

10:08.042 --> 10:09.109
you are 16 years old.

10:09.177 --> 10:10.911
Your frontal lobe is not developed yet.

10:10.979 --> 10:12.479
I have more brain than you do.

10:12.547 --> 10:15.082
And my brain knows what it's
like to be judged by that woman.

10:15.149 --> 10:17.250
Well, I know that it's
better to be out than in.

10:17.318 --> 10:19.486
And whatever that woman
throws at me, I can take it.

10:19.554 --> 10:20.420
And I'm going to bed.

10:20.488 --> 10:23.623
♪ ♪

10:25.093 --> 10:27.094
You look like a Mormon's eighth wife.

10:27.161 --> 10:30.530
I don't care. I made $124 today.

10:31.532 --> 10:33.867
[Snorts]

10:33.935 --> 10:36.470
[Sighs] So, how is this going to work?

10:36.537 --> 10:37.771
It's not a big deal.

10:37.839 --> 10:40.007
It's six hours, and
then my mother goes home.

10:40.074 --> 10:41.441
What about next time when she visits?

10:41.509 --> 10:43.010
What are we gonna do when
I live in a new place?

10:43.077 --> 10:44.444
We'll worry about that then.

10:44.512 --> 10:46.980
What if you've got a boyfriend?
What if I've got a girlfriend?

10:47.048 --> 10:48.768
How am I gonna explain
spending the night...

10:48.783 --> 10:51.100
A threesome... With my
ex-wife and a pillow?

10:51.347 --> 10:53.887
All I'm saying is that
I think Kenny is right.

10:53.955 --> 10:55.522
I mean, why don't you just tell her?

10:55.590 --> 10:57.657
Kenny doesn't know what it's
like to have a difficult mother.

10:57.725 --> 10:58.992
[Chuckles]

11:02.864 --> 11:04.865
Eileen: No, the cab is for my mother,

11:04.932 --> 11:06.633
and I don't really
know how to phrase this,

11:06.701 --> 11:10.003
but if you could send your most, um...

11:10.071 --> 11:12.372
Uh, patriotic driver.

11:12.440 --> 11:14.241
- See you soon.
- So?

11:14.308 --> 11:15.675
Good morning, Mom.

11:15.743 --> 11:17.210
Your taxi's on the way.

11:17.278 --> 11:19.246
I'll bet you're excited
to be heading home.

11:19.313 --> 11:20.280
I am.

11:20.348 --> 11:22.382
And, Kenny, I've decided I'm glad

11:22.450 --> 11:23.917
you told me about being gay.

11:23.985 --> 11:25.152
Wait. You are?

11:25.219 --> 11:26.553
Yes.

11:26.621 --> 11:28.088
Admitting you have a problem

11:28.156 --> 11:30.023
is the first step towards fixing it.

11:30.091 --> 11:31.371
Looks like she has a whole list.

11:31.426 --> 11:32.826
Yeah, no, I'm not really sure

11:32.894 --> 11:34.528
it's something that
you can fix, Grandma.

11:34.595 --> 11:36.196
Well, that's just the thing. It is.

11:36.264 --> 11:38.098
For example, whenever
you feel a gay impulse,

11:38.166 --> 11:39.266
take a cold shower.

11:39.333 --> 11:40.667
Mnh-mnh. I prefer baths.

11:40.735 --> 11:43.036
So did the Romans, and we
know what happened to them.

11:43.104 --> 11:45.405
Also, write with your
less dominant hand.

11:45.473 --> 11:48.775
It'll fix that hinky wiring in
your brain that makes you gay.

11:48.843 --> 11:50.677
You know, again, I'm not
really sure that's how it works.

11:50.745 --> 11:54.681
Perhaps most helpful...

11:54.749 --> 11:56.149
I'm gonna send you to this.

11:58.286 --> 11:59.719
Um...

11:59.787 --> 12:02.055
A gay conversion camp?

12:02.123 --> 12:03.557
Oh, camp sounds fun.

12:03.624 --> 12:05.692
The rest seems a little odd.

12:05.760 --> 12:07.961
You'll spend two weeks in
the woods with other boys

12:08.029 --> 12:10.197
that have the same affliction you do.

12:10.264 --> 12:12.365
<i>Hmm... </i>

12:12.433 --> 12:17.104
Mmm. These heterosexual
s'mores are delicious.

12:17.171 --> 12:20.307
They're so messy. I
got some on my shirt.

12:20.374 --> 12:23.143
- ♪ I can't believe ♪
- Oh, I spilled, too.

12:23.211 --> 12:25.278
We better go wash off at the lake.

12:25.346 --> 12:27.214
- Good idea.
- Meet you there!

12:27.281 --> 12:29.116
[Cheers and laughter]

12:29.183 --> 12:31.585
Mm. Two weeks in the woods
with a bunch of gay boys?

12:31.652 --> 12:32.919
You're right.

12:32.987 --> 12:34.955
I think that's probably the
best thing for me right now.

12:35.022 --> 12:37.757
Uh, I think Kenny's gonna be
very busy this summer, Mom.

12:37.825 --> 12:39.993
I don't think either of you is
taking this seriously enough.

12:40.061 --> 12:43.130
All right. There's a cab
out front for you, Agnes.

12:43.197 --> 12:45.037
How about one more
mustache kiss before you go?

12:45.066 --> 12:46.299
I'm not going anywhere.

12:46.367 --> 12:49.169
Eileen, you've let this
situation get out of control.

12:49.237 --> 12:51.571
I'm staying here until
I save Kenny's soul

12:51.639 --> 12:53.106
from eternal damnation.

12:53.174 --> 12:55.609
What's the timeline
on something like that?

12:55.676 --> 12:57.811
Could be weeks. Could be months.

12:57.879 --> 13:01.014
It depends on how much sin
is hiding in this house.

13:01.082 --> 13:03.817
<i>Mom can't fake being
married for that long.</i>

13:03.885 --> 13:05.619
Mom, you can't stay here.

13:05.686 --> 13:08.188
You didn't even bring any clothes.

13:08.256 --> 13:09.489
<i>Good one.</i>

13:09.557 --> 13:11.077
I'll wash out my turtleneck every night

13:11.092 --> 13:12.559
and borrow some of your panties.

13:14.061 --> 13:16.129
I'll take that mustache kiss now.

13:17.331 --> 13:18.298
[Sighs]

