13:32.634 --> 13:33.734
- Mom?
- Look away!

13:33.802 --> 13:35.336
Mom, what are you doing?

13:35.404 --> 13:38.072
I'm eating gay cake on the toilet.

13:38.140 --> 13:40.374
Mom, you have to tell Grandma the truth.

13:40.442 --> 13:41.609
I have fought all my life

13:41.676 --> 13:43.878
for just a little bit of
approval from that woman.

13:43.945 --> 13:46.080
If I tell her now that
my marriage is a failure,

13:46.148 --> 13:47.214
that will never happen.

13:47.282 --> 13:48.916
You can do this, and I can help you.

13:48.984 --> 13:50.985
I have successfully
come out three times.

13:51.052 --> 13:53.220
And which time do you think
was the most successful?

13:53.288 --> 13:55.408
When you outed yourself in
front of the entire parish?

13:55.424 --> 13:57.158
When you gay-bashed yourself at school?

13:57.225 --> 13:59.059
Or when you broke Grandma?

13:59.127 --> 14:00.694
I had a better plan.

14:00.762 --> 14:03.597
I was gonna soften you up by
cooking your favorite meal,

14:03.665 --> 14:06.066
and then I was gonna
mention all the famous people

14:06.134 --> 14:07.435
you love who are gay.

14:07.502 --> 14:08.469
What? Who?

14:08.537 --> 14:09.403
We don't need to do that right now.

14:09.471 --> 14:10.404
George Clooney?

14:10.472 --> 14:11.605
Don't tell me. I don't want to know.

14:11.673 --> 14:13.574
Anyway, once I got you used to the idea

14:13.642 --> 14:15.342
that you already loved gay people,

14:15.410 --> 14:17.077
I was gonna tell you about me.

14:17.145 --> 14:19.280
You think that would work for divorce?

14:19.347 --> 14:21.182
Well, it's got to, because...

14:21.249 --> 14:22.216
[Sighs]

14:22.284 --> 14:24.251
This is not.

14:24.319 --> 14:25.753
Oh, mother.

14:25.821 --> 14:28.522
Is that sink ice cream?

14:28.590 --> 14:31.091
Mom...

14:31.159 --> 14:32.760
[Fingers snap] Drop it.

14:32.828 --> 14:35.796
♪ ♪

14:35.864 --> 14:37.131
When does she have the time?

14:37.199 --> 14:38.399
Good. Shannon, you're here.

14:38.467 --> 14:39.467
What stinks?

14:39.534 --> 14:40.501
Mom's trying to soften up Grandma

14:40.569 --> 14:41.936
by cooking her corned beef and cabbage.

14:42.003 --> 14:43.771
Oh, good. I thought we got skunked.

14:43.839 --> 14:45.172
Eileen, I'm so proud of you.

14:45.240 --> 14:47.908
And I fully support you
telling your mom the truth.

14:47.976 --> 14:50.211
I am, however, gonna
try and get Agnes to sign

14:50.278 --> 14:52.798
this legal zoom document locking
down those Bears tickets first.

14:52.814 --> 14:53.914
Totally get it.

14:53.982 --> 14:55.502
And I will do everything I can to help.

14:55.517 --> 14:57.117
Okay. This is how it's gonna go down.

14:57.185 --> 14:58.285
Shannon, you get in there

14:58.353 --> 15:00.054
and you give her that
completed coloring book.

15:00.121 --> 15:02.056
Jimmy, show her that
you finished the puzzle.

15:02.123 --> 15:03.557
Yeah, actually, Shannon
finished it for me.

15:03.625 --> 15:05.125
Shannon: You can take the credit.

15:05.193 --> 15:07.261
I'm already wearing her
purple corduroy overalls.

15:07.329 --> 15:09.296
Mom, she's had three glasses of Sherry.

15:09.364 --> 15:10.931
She's in there smiling at nothing.

15:10.999 --> 15:12.166
Now, you get in there,

15:12.234 --> 15:14.134
and you tell her how much you hate Dad.

15:14.202 --> 15:16.237
That's right. Hey, don't sugarcoat it.

15:16.304 --> 15:17.771
Let's go.

15:17.839 --> 15:18.672
One, two, three.

15:18.740 --> 15:19.807
All: Corned beef!

15:19.875 --> 15:21.642
The scandal isn't that
she's black, Grandma.

15:21.710 --> 15:22.977
It's just the name of the show.

15:23.044 --> 15:24.512
Well, it's confusing.

15:26.381 --> 15:29.617
So, uh, do you remember
when Joan and Ted Kennedy

15:29.684 --> 15:30.851
got divorced?

15:30.919 --> 15:32.253
Mm, the Kennedys. Saints.

15:32.320 --> 15:33.621
Yes, but they got a divorce.

15:33.688 --> 15:35.856
I think the pope
pardoned Ted on that one.

15:35.924 --> 15:38.626
And Alex Trebek, by
the way. Also divorced.

15:38.693 --> 15:40.427
So he could live with his mother.

15:40.495 --> 15:42.463
[Chuckles] What are you getting at?

15:42.531 --> 15:44.365
Why all this divorce talk?

15:44.432 --> 15:46.200
Um...

15:46.268 --> 15:48.168
I have something to tell you.

15:48.236 --> 15:50.304
Before you do, I have
to tell you something.

15:50.372 --> 15:52.840
Eileen, this corned beef is really good.

15:52.908 --> 15:54.475
- But?
- No but.

15:54.543 --> 15:57.111
You have made a lovely meal. Hmm.

15:57.178 --> 16:00.281
♪ ♪

16:00.348 --> 16:02.316
Oh, but I cut you off.

16:02.384 --> 16:03.684
What were you saying?

16:03.752 --> 16:05.553
<i>This is your moment.</i>

16:05.620 --> 16:08.689
<i>You softened her up. Do it, Mom. Do it.</i>

16:08.757 --> 16:10.724
I, um...

16:10.792 --> 16:12.560
I was going to say...

16:12.627 --> 16:16.363
That, um...

16:16.431 --> 16:17.665
I have to get dessert.

16:17.732 --> 16:19.700
<i>Or... don't.</i>

16:19.768 --> 16:21.402
Am I eating the same thing as Grandma?

16:21.469 --> 16:23.404
Yes.

16:23.471 --> 16:24.171
What happened?

16:24.239 --> 16:25.139
[Sighs]

16:25.206 --> 16:27.146
All that woman ever talks about

16:27.147 --> 16:28.642
are the two things I've
done wrong in my life.

16:28.710 --> 16:29.944
The first was being born,

16:30.011 --> 16:32.379
the second one was getting
pregnant out of wedlock.

16:32.447 --> 16:36.350
I have been waiting my whole life

16:36.418 --> 16:39.253
for the feeling I just got from
that corned-beef compliment.

16:39.321 --> 16:41.088
And let me tell you something.

16:41.156 --> 16:43.390
It's worth staying in the closet for.

16:43.458 --> 16:44.758
And I'm not saying this to hurt you,

16:44.826 --> 16:47.761
but the corned beef
really wasn't that good.

16:47.829 --> 16:49.263
She's just drunk.

16:49.331 --> 16:51.665
I don't care if she stays
drunk for the rest of her life.

16:51.733 --> 16:53.334
I like her this way.

16:53.401 --> 16:57.271
<i>I guess she wasn't ready, but
it's not for me to judge.</i>

16:57.339 --> 17:00.207
<i>Everyone has to come
out in their own time.</i>

17:00.275 --> 17:01.408
Oh, there it is.

17:01.476 --> 17:02.610
Show me the pudding.

17:02.677 --> 17:04.243
Oh, is that my favorite?

17:04.311 --> 17:06.046
Bread-and-butter
pudding. It sure is.

17:06.114 --> 17:08.015
Oh, Agnes. I thought
I was your favorite?

17:08.083 --> 17:10.050
Oh, Pat, you're a rascal.

17:10.117 --> 17:12.419
Well, Eileen, you have
really outdone yourself.

17:12.487 --> 17:13.686
Oh, thanks, Mom.

17:13.755 --> 17:16.290
Kenny helped with the dessert.

17:16.358 --> 17:17.523
It looks a little dry.

17:17.592 --> 17:19.425
Do you want some sauce, Grandma?

17:19.493 --> 17:20.794
No, thank you.

17:20.862 --> 17:23.063
You want somebody less
saucy to give you sauce?

17:23.131 --> 17:24.897
I know you think I'm a silly old woman

17:24.965 --> 17:26.934
and you've been mocking
me and my beliefs,

17:27.002 --> 17:29.069
but even if you don't care what I think,

17:29.137 --> 17:31.105
you should care about what God thinks.

17:31.172 --> 17:32.406
I do.

17:32.474 --> 17:35.242
No, you don't. God doesn't accept you.

17:35.310 --> 17:37.911
He thinks you're broken, and I do, too.

17:37.979 --> 17:41.415
<i>I didn't think anything Grandma
said could upset me,</i>

17:41.483 --> 17:43.283
<i>but I was wrong.</i>

17:43.351 --> 17:44.485
That's enough, Mom.

17:44.552 --> 17:45.886
My son is not broken,

17:45.954 --> 17:47.921
and if you want to talk about someone

17:47.989 --> 17:50.491
who's not accepted by
God, you can talk about me.

17:53.461 --> 17:54.828
Pat and I are getting a divorce.

17:54.896 --> 17:56.730
That's right. And it's
not her fault, Agnes.

17:56.798 --> 17:58.065
It was a mutual decision.

17:58.133 --> 17:59.366
That's right.

17:59.434 --> 18:01.394
So, you can say whatever
you want to say now, Mom.

18:02.537 --> 18:03.370
Whoa.

18:04.372 --> 18:05.773
Kenny: Are you choking?

18:06.808 --> 18:08.308
Is this what we're doing?

18:08.376 --> 18:09.736
We're letting God take out Grandma?

18:09.744 --> 18:10.844
No!

18:10.912 --> 18:12.312
[Choking]

18:12.380 --> 18:14.515
Oh!

18:14.582 --> 18:16.784
I told you it was dry.

18:16.851 --> 18:20.087
♪ ♪

18:22.357 --> 18:23.857
[Coughs]

18:23.925 --> 18:26.326
Come on, everyone. We need
to get to church early.

18:26.394 --> 18:27.594
We have a lot of work to do.

18:27.662 --> 18:29.382
Let's get going. You
heard your grandmother.

18:29.431 --> 18:31.498
I want this family in the front pew

18:31.566 --> 18:34.501
so the holy spirit can
blast us right in the face.

18:34.569 --> 18:37.337
Jimmy: Oh, in the splash zone.

18:37.405 --> 18:40.007
Dad, why are we going to
church with this woman?

18:40.075 --> 18:43.711
Bears tickets. Why are you doing it?

18:43.778 --> 18:44.945
This is ridiculous.

18:45.013 --> 18:46.653
Everybody is acting
like nothing happened.

18:46.681 --> 18:48.182
It's classic Irish-Catholic denial.

18:48.249 --> 18:49.450
It's the one thing they love

18:49.517 --> 18:50.718
more than corned beef and cabbage.

18:50.785 --> 18:51.885
[Chuckles]

18:51.953 --> 18:53.554
No, it's not.

18:53.621 --> 18:56.123
Oh, my God. I'm doing it.

18:56.191 --> 18:57.458
I call back right!

18:57.525 --> 19:00.527
At least Shannon, Jimmy, and
I can still take communion.

19:00.595 --> 19:01.762
You sure can.

19:01.830 --> 19:03.864
I hope the foreign
priest isn't leading mass.

19:03.932 --> 19:05.899
I can barely understand a word he says.

19:05.967 --> 19:08.068
Those New York accents
can be pretty crazy.

19:08.136 --> 19:09.403
You missed the turn.

19:09.471 --> 19:10.571
Nope. I didn't.

19:10.638 --> 19:13.207
Why are we stopping at cousin Gary's?

19:13.274 --> 19:15.375
I've decided that your visit's over

19:15.443 --> 19:18.212
and it's time for you to
learn about Sikh culture.

19:18.279 --> 19:19.747
They just celebrated Hola Mohalla.

19:19.814 --> 19:20.981
You should ask him about it.

19:21.049 --> 19:22.382
- Damn.
- Damn.

19:22.450 --> 19:23.517
<i>Whoa.</i>

19:23.585 --> 19:24.752
<i>It's not Grandma Agnes</i>

19:24.819 --> 19:26.520
<i>who's a straight-up Catholic gangsta.</i>

19:26.588 --> 19:27.588
<i>It's my mom.</i>

19:27.655 --> 19:28.589
What?

19:28.656 --> 19:29.957
I'm sorry, Mom.

19:30.024 --> 19:32.593
I can handle your judgment
because I'm used to it.

19:32.660 --> 19:35.929
But I just won't have you
doing that to my children.

19:35.997 --> 19:38.065
You're not welcome back to our house

19:38.133 --> 19:40.434
until you respect everyone in my family.

19:40.502 --> 19:43.470
♪ ♪

19:45.240 --> 19:46.600
Aren't you gonna help me out, Pat?

19:46.641 --> 19:49.176
Uh, I'll take "no" for $400, Agnes.

19:49.244 --> 19:51.345
You can forget about
those Bears tickets.

19:51.412 --> 19:53.247
Well, then I'm gonna
shave off my mustache.

19:53.314 --> 19:56.717
That's the most
disappointing thing of all.

19:56.785 --> 19:58.619
[Sighs]

20:00.421 --> 20:01.421
[Door slams]

20:01.489 --> 20:02.456
[Door opens]

20:02.524 --> 20:03.791
Hi, Agnes. Hello, welcome.

20:03.858 --> 20:04.892
Ugh.

20:04.959 --> 20:06.860
Nama... ow!

20:08.463 --> 20:12.399
I did not see that coming, Mom.

20:12.467 --> 20:13.600
Thank you.

20:13.668 --> 20:15.602
Coming out is really terrifying.

20:15.670 --> 20:17.171
You are very brave.

20:19.641 --> 20:20.641
What should we do now?

20:20.708 --> 20:22.810
Well...

20:22.877 --> 20:25.379
I'd still like to go to church.

20:25.446 --> 20:28.782
All right. Let's go to
church, take communion...

20:28.850 --> 20:31.618
- [Engine starts]
- And burst into flames.

20:31.686 --> 20:34.254
We should probably confess
we almost killed Grandma.

20:34.322 --> 20:36.757
♪ ♪

20:37.966 --> 20:42.088
- Mm. Ellen DeGeneres.
- I know that one. Who else?

20:42.156 --> 20:43.756
Mm, that guy you love
on "The Good Wife."

20:43.824 --> 20:45.692
- What?
- Yeah, also, he's Scottish.

20:45.759 --> 20:47.560
What?!

20:47.628 --> 20:49.929
You know, that was really cool the way

20:49.997 --> 20:51.864
you outed yourself to Grandma.

20:51.932 --> 20:53.333
Oh, I was so terrified.

20:53.400 --> 20:54.701
Was it that scary for you?

20:54.768 --> 20:57.737
No. But that's 'cause I have
a better mom than you do.

20:57.805 --> 21:00.940
♪ ♪

21:01.008 --> 21:01.941
Mm!

21:02.009 --> 21:03.676
Your hairdresser, Timothy...

21:03.744 --> 21:07.013
- Mm?
- Ironically straight.

21:07.081 --> 21:09.248
I don't understand anything.

21:09.316 --> 21:11.384
[Dog barking in distance]

21:11.452 --> 21:12.919
Mmm.

21:12.987 --> 21:14.721
Orange one's the best.

21:14.788 --> 21:16.923
Mmm. They all taste the same to me.

21:16.991 --> 21:18.358
Really?

21:18.425 --> 21:19.926
Yeah. I mean, what's the point?

